Final answer: 
Frontend Implementation Complete for project_id=1

## Feature Groups Implemented

### 1. Live Dashboard (User Story 6)
- **Page:** `src/pages/DashboardPage.tsx`
- Shows queue overview cards (Total Waiting, Critical, High, Medium, Low, Avg Wait)
- Patient queue table with name, urgency badge, arrival time, estimated wait, status
- Auto-refreshes every 10 seconds for real-time updates
- Loading, error, and empty states handled

### 2. Patient Registration with Urgency Assignment (User Stories 1 & 2)
- **Page:** `src/pages/RegisterPatientPage.tsx`
- Form with patient name, symptoms (textarea), and urgency level dropdown (1-5)
- Validation for required fields before submission
- Navigates to dashboard on success
- Error handling when backend is unavailable

### 3. Queue Management with Dequeue (User Story 5)
- **Page:** `src/pages/QueuePage.tsx`
- Shows sorted patient queue table
- "Dequeue Next Patient" button that removes highest-priority patient
- Result feedback after dequeue operation
- Loading, error, and empty states handled

### 4. Shared Components
- `src/components/Layout.tsx` — Sticky frosted-glass nav with links to all pages
- `src/components/UrgencyBadge.tsx` — Color-coded urgency badge (Critical=red, High=orange, Medium=blue, Low=grey, Routine=light 
grey)

### 5. API Service Layer
- `src/api/services.ts` — Axios client mapping all backend endpoints:
  - `GET /api/queue/{id}/overview` — Queue overview stats
  - `GET /api/queue/{id}/patients` — Patient queue list
  - `POST /api/patient` — Register new patient
  - `GET /api/patient/{id}` — Get patient details
  - `PUT /api/patient/{id}` — Update patient
  - `DELETE /api/patient/{id}` — Delete patient
  - `DELETE /api/patient_queue/{id}` — Dequeue patient
  - `GET /api/patient_queue/{id}` — Get queue entry
  - `PUT /api/patient_queue/{id}` — Update queue entry
  - `DELETE /api/patient_queue/{id}` — Delete queue entry

### 6. Types
- `src/types/index.ts` — TypeScript interfaces for Patient, PatientQueue, QueueOverview, RegisterPatientRequest, DequeueResponse

## Build: ✅ Success (TypeScript + Vite production build)
## Tests: 7 passed, 0 failed
- DashboardPage: renders without crashing, shows Dashboard heading
- RegisterPatientPage: renders without crashing, shows Register Patient heading
- QueuePage: renders without crashing, shows Queue Management heading
- App: renders without crashing

